00:05:37.289 --> 00:05:41.919
a database of protected material. YouTube
scans the uploaded content looking for a match

00:05:41.919 --> 00:05:46.069
in the database. When there is a match, rights
holders can elect to either block or remove

00:05:46.069 --> 00:05:49.609
the offending material, or monetize the video
by running ads against it.

00:05:49.609 --> 00:05:53.460
Though content I.D. seems to have slowed all
